main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted by M.P. and Mrs. J.P. Chamberlain on June 12, 1961.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, star-like object emitting a bluish-grey light and remained stationary for some time,It was observed through binoculars to have an elongated delta wing shape,Approximately 30-40 feet in length,The object moved off rapidly towards the North East before disappearing,There was no noise reported from the object.
sighted object: bright, star-like object emitting bluish-grey light
location: Milne Bay District, Papua New Guinea
